text:
bug on batik SVG DOM implementation on the SVGSVGElement.createSVGTransform

The SVGTransform returned from SVGSVGElement.createSVGTransform is not correct.
The type returned is 0 (SVG_TRANSFORM_UNKNOWN) where the SVG specification says
it should return 1 (SVG_TRANSFORM_MATRIX)

Some possible fix:
1) on package org.apache.batik.dom.svg;

class SVGOMSVGElement

 public SVGTransform           createSVGTransform (  ) {
    SVGMatrix matrix = createSVGMatrix();
    return createSVGTransformFromMatrix (matrix );
 }

2) on package org.apache.batik.dom.svg;
class AbstractSVGTransform on the constructor set the type into 1
(SVG_TRANSFORM_MATRIX)
